00:22:15,667 --> 00:22:18,158
Isn't it once it is
transplanted, it'll be fine?

271
00:22:19,604 --> 00:22:20,969
When healthy bone
marrow are transplanted,

272
00:22:21,306 --> 00:22:23,001
the new blood produced will
contain no cancer cells.

273
00:22:23,342 --> 00:22:24,604
Of course, the disease will be cured.

274
00:22:27,012 --> 00:22:28,946
But, it isn't that easy.

275
00:22:29,481 --> 00:22:30,209
Why?

276
00:22:32,284 --> 00:22:33,751
Bone marrow transplant
is very expensive.

277
00:22:34,619 --> 00:22:36,246
It needs two to three
hundred thousands dollars.

278
00:22:36,788 --> 00:22:39,188
Also, it must be matched.

279
00:22:39,424 --> 00:22:41,551
It isn't easy to get
the right one to match.

280
00:22:42,060 --> 00:22:44,028
The chance is only one in ten thousand.

281
00:22:45,063 --> 00:22:46,758
The right match is very difficult.

282
00:22:47,532 --> 00:22:49,966
Haven't you seem there are
so many children waiting?

283
00:22:52,170 --> 00:22:53,296
What can I do?

284
00:22:54,773 --> 00:22:57,207
Nothing, just wait.

285
00:22:58,176 --> 00:22:59,302
Depends your luck.

286
00:24:02,441 --> 00:24:04,773
Who? It's me.

287
00:24:06,778 --> 00:24:07,608
Mrs Chan.

288
00:24:10,749 --> 00:24:11,738
What's the matter with you?

289
00:24:12,050 --> 00:24:14,041
I am telling you Fai has blood cancer.

290
00:24:14,719 --> 00:24:16,186
Blood cancer? Yes.

291
00:24:16,354 --> 00:24:17,252
Can't be.

292
00:24:17,622 --> 00:24:18,611
I also don't believe.

293
00:24:19,157 --> 00:24:21,717
Then, we'd better quickly
donate the blood to him.

294
00:24:22,027 --> 00:24:22,652
Is that work?

295
00:24:22,828 --> 00:24:24,159
Of course.

296
00:24:24,396 --> 00:24:26,421
Well. You all wait for
me tomorrow morning.

297
00:24:26,665 --> 00:24:28,098
We can go to the hospital together.

298
00:24:28,266 --> 00:24:30,200
You go now. Okay.

299
00:24:34,139 --> 00:24:34,935
Officer

300
00:24:35,474 --> 00:24:38,136
Luk Fai's bone marrow exam
report is not so optimistic.

301
00:24:38,610 --> 00:24:40,635
I know. I've seen the report.

302
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:43,971
Make an appointment for
me with Luk Fai's mum.

303
00:24:44,616 --> 00:24:45,981
I want to find out,

304
00:24:46,451 --> 00:24:48,578
how much psychological
preparation has she got.

305
00:24:48,753 --> 00:24:51,187
Okay. I'll inform Mrs
Luk as soon as possible.

306
00:24:52,457 --> 00:24:55,187
Send Luk Fai's genes arrangement
information out quickly.

307
00:24:55,861 --> 00:24:56,828
It has been sent off.

308
00:24:57,095 --> 00:24:59,928
Including Guangzhou,
Jinan, Wuhan & Chengdu.

309
00:25:00,732 --> 00:25:01,721
What about Taiwan & Hong Kong?

310
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:02,728
Were also sent.

311
00:25:22,153 --> 00:25:23,120
My boy.

312
00:25:24,356 --> 00:25:25,653
Were you good yesterday?

313
00:25:27,225 --> 00:25:28,089
Did you sleep well?

314
00:25:29,494 --> 00:25:31,519
You know? Grandpa is
very much thinking of you.

315
00:25:33,465 --> 00:25:34,625
Don't you want me?

316
00:25:35,233 --> 00:25:37,428
Are you sure you don't want me?

317
00:25:38,236 --> 00:25:39,464
See what I have brought for you?

318
00:25:42,407 --> 00:25:44,466
Fai, you see.

319
00:25:44,776 --> 00:25:46,403
Mum has to go back
to look after Grandpa.

320
00:25:46,578 --> 00:25:48,409
And also have to hand in
the script to Auntie Wong.

321
00:25:48,580 --> 00:25:49,342
You know?

322
00:25:51,316 --> 00:25:54,342
Mum, when can I really go?

323
00:25:56,121 --> 00:25:58,612
I think a few more days.

324
00:25:58,924 --> 00:26:00,323
Anyway, Mum will accompany
with you these few days,

325
00:26:00,492 --> 00:26:01,390
okay?

326
00:26:01,793 --> 00:26:03,693
No, I don't want to
stay in the hospital.

327
00:26:03,995 --> 00:26:04,984
I want to go home.

328
00:26:05,764 --> 00:26:07,925
Fai, you're the best.

329
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:10,397
Mum has told you earlier,

330
00:26:10,602 --> 00:26:13,469
there's no other choice except
staying in the hospital if you're sick.

331
00:26:14,072 --> 00:26:16,063
I know you're very bored.

332
00:26:17,208 --> 00:26:18,197
Okay.

333
00:26:18,510 --> 00:26:20,068
What about you speak to Dr Lee.

334
00:26:20,312 --> 00:26:22,837
If he can let you go, I
bring you home right away.

335
00:26:23,281 --> 00:26:24,373
What do you think?

336
00:26:26,351 --> 00:26:28,751
You know, Mum is very much
like to bring you home.

337
00:26:29,120 --> 00:26:31,850
Without you at home, Mum
has lost an assistant.

338
00:26:32,257 --> 00:26:34,225
You see, no one will do
the massage for Grandpa.

339
00:26:34,626 --> 00:26:36,958
And no one will give medicine
to Grandpa too, right?

340
00:26:38,330 --> 00:26:41,094
Mum, what diseases have I got?

341
00:26:42,233 --> 00:26:44,167
Why is it my whole body has no strength?

342
00:27:01,086 --> 00:27:02,747
Mum, where're you going?

343
00:27:04,356 --> 00:27:06,847
Mum has to go the toilet
and will be back right away.

344
00:27:28,079 --> 00:27:29,740
Why are you here? Are
you looking for me?

345
00:27:30,515 --> 00:27:32,346
Beijing has just admitted a new patient.

346
00:27:32,651 --> 00:27:33,640
A boy who is eight years old.

347
00:27:34,719 --> 00:27:35,413
What's the name?

348
00:27:35,587 --> 00:27:36,554
Called Luk Fai.

349
00:27:36,888 --> 00:27:37,877
Luk Fai?

350
00:27:39,290 --> 00:27:42,316
Right, there was a girl called Yin Yin,

351
00:27:42,694 --> 00:27:43,683
Has she got the right match?

352
00:27:44,195 --> 00:27:45,219
Not yet.

353
00:27:45,830 --> 00:27:47,229
Still on the waiting list.

354
00:27:48,033 --> 00:27:49,625
The blood samples are so few.

355
00:27:51,436 --> 00:27:52,630
I think it's very difficult.

356
00:27:53,204 --> 00:27:56,571
Sometimes, this job do
make people desperate.

357
00:27:58,309 --> 00:27:59,139
It's not.

358
00:28:00,011 --> 00:28:02,502
In fact, I think no matter
how many times of failure,

359
00:28:02,714 --> 00:28:03,840
and if only one is successful,

360
00:28:04,182 --> 00:28:05,740
this job is still worthwhile.

361
00:28:06,885 --> 00:28:07,977
I understand.

362
00:28:09,354 --> 00:28:10,616
But there're so many
people don't understand.

363
00:28:11,022 --> 00:28:12,922
Why are you giving up
your original doctor's work

364
00:28:13,191 --> 00:28:14,886
and go to work for the
Care Unit as volunteer?

365
00:28:17,662 --> 00:28:18,890
I also don't know.

366
00:28:19,264 --> 00:28:20,629
I just like this job.

367
00:28:20,799 --> 00:28:22,198
I work happily.

368
00:28:23,268 --> 00:28:24,360
Dr Kao, sorry.

369
00:28:24,536 --> 00:28:25,525
Patient in the Operating
Theatre is ready.

370
00:28:25,704 --> 00:28:26,966
Can you go and have a look? Okay.

371
00:28:27,138 --> 00:28:27,968
I'm off first.

372
00:28:44,622 --> 00:28:45,611
Who do you want?

373
00:28:46,591 --> 00:28:47,819
I...

374
00:28:48,526 --> 00:28:51,791
That day my Mum and I saw you to
have hair cut outside the door.

375
00:28:54,099 --> 00:28:55,760
Do you stay in this hospital too?

376
00:28:57,602 --> 00:28:58,933
What's wrong with you?

377
00:28:59,871 --> 00:29:01,964
Why did you let your mum

378
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:03,639
to shave your head?

379
00:29:08,480 --> 00:29:11,711
It's because my disease
would cause my hair to shed.

380
00:29:12,383 --> 00:29:13,850
It hurts my mum.

381
00:29:14,452 --> 00:29:16,386
So, I let my mum to have it shaved.

382
00:29:19,591 --> 00:29:21,320
Are you also having haemophilia?

383
00:29:23,495 --> 00:29:24,928
I don't know.

384
00:29:27,799 --> 00:29:31,599
You look pretty healthy
and same as I was.

385
00:29:32,403 --> 00:29:33,927
But since you stay here,

386
00:29:34,839 --> 00:29:36,568
it must be the same.

387
00:29:37,475 --> 00:29:38,965
Don't you know about it?

388
00:29:39,944 --> 00:29:42,640
Haemophilia can whiten
the color of the blood.

389
00:29:43,615 --> 00:29:45,776
When the blood is damaged,
would be hair shed?

390
00:29:47,919 --> 00:29:49,477
You'll find out more in the future.

391
00:29:52,290 --> 00:29:54,121
I think you should be okay.

392
00:29:58,429 --> 00:30:00,863
Sister, your picture is very pretty.

393
00:30:02,333 --> 00:30:03,300
Do you like it?

394
00:30:04,002 --> 00:30:04,764
Yes!

395
00:30:05,136 --> 00:30:06,433
Then, I give it to you.

396
00:30:06,971 --> 00:30:07,733
Thank you, sister.

397
00:30:10,041 --> 00:30:11,702
Since I was admitted
to hospital till now,

398
00:30:12,410 --> 00:30:14,571
I carry this pair of shoes everyday.

399
00:30:15,580 --> 00:30:19,880
Today, it's the first time I wear it.

400
00:30:43,174 --> 00:30:46,007
Sister, you danced very well!

401
00:30:46,911 --> 00:30:47,935
But, you have to promise me,

402
00:30:48,413 --> 00:30:50,176
if you really become a Ballet dancer,

403
00:30:50,648 --> 00:30:52,639
you must invite me to
see your "Swan Lake" show.

404
00:30:53,017 --> 00:30:54,314
I won't forget.

405
00:30:55,687 --> 00:30:59,817
That day, I'll invite Dad, Mum

406
00:31:00,091 --> 00:31:01,183
and also you

407
00:31:01,726 --> 00:31:03,318
to see my performance.

408
00:31:04,229 --> 00:31:07,562
We surely can wait for
that day to come, right?

409
00:31:07,866 --> 00:31:08,764
No problem.

410
00:31:10,902 --> 00:31:11,891
What?

411
00:31:12,437 --> 00:31:14,701
We make a deal for our promises.

412
00:31:15,306 --> 00:31:17,035
Then, we both can't change our mind.

413
00:31:19,577 --> 00:31:24,037
Done and no change for one hundred year.

414
00:31:25,416 --> 00:31:28,283
I'll wait for you to
become the real No. 10.

415
00:31:28,653 --> 00:31:31,816
Then, you should invite
me to see the World Cup.

416
00:31:32,190 --> 00:31:32,952
No problem.

417
00:31:35,393 --> 00:31:37,623
Sister, your hand is very cold.

418
00:31:39,397 --> 00:31:40,762
I can't stand cold weather.

419
00:31:41,866 --> 00:31:44,699
Then, you come close to my
body. I can stand the cold.

420
00:31:48,206 --> 00:31:49,468
Feel warmer now?

421
00:31:50,608 --> 00:31:52,701
Will you forget me? Fai.

422
00:31:53,411 --> 00:31:55,811
No, when we leave the hospital,

423
00:31:56,247 --> 00:31:58,738
you're still my sister
and I'm your brother.

424
00:31:59,584 --> 00:32:02,382
Okay. We'll keep as it is

425
00:32:02,921 --> 00:32:04,479
until we become old.

426
00:32:14,332 --> 00:32:16,800
Please don't worry, we must try our best

427
00:32:17,068 --> 00:32:18,194
to cure your child.

428
00:32:18,469 --> 00:32:19,993
How can I not to worry?

429
00:32:20,371 --> 00:32:22,305
Dr Lee, I'm his mum.

430
00:32:22,607 --> 00:32:23,938
But I look like an idiot now,

431
00:32:24,108 --> 00:32:24,904
I know nothing.

432
00:32:25,209 --> 00:32:26,073
How's my son?

433
00:32:26,244 --> 00:32:27,734
What will happen later on?

434
00:32:27,979 --> 00:32:30,106
I don't know anything.
How can I not to worry?

435
00:32:30,848 --> 00:32:33,578
Dr Lee, can you guarantee
to save my son's life?

436
00:32:33,851 --> 00:32:36,115
I can't guarantee anything for you.

437
00:32:36,287 --> 00:32:37,481
But you must believe me.

438
00:32:37,855 --> 00:32:40,119
We'll try our very
best to cure your son.

439
00:32:40,925 --> 00:32:44,019
This is our duty as
doctor, you understand?

440
00:32:44,762 --> 00:32:45,956
Don't worry!

441
00:32:49,968 --> 00:32:52,300
The dreadful haemophilia,
accordingly to my knowledge,

442
00:32:52,770 --> 00:32:56,137
western medicine has a method
for the bone marrow transplant.

443
00:32:56,975 --> 00:32:58,840
That's currently
considered to be better.

444
00:33:00,278 --> 00:33:01,939
Having the experience of hospital life,

445
00:33:03,114 --> 00:33:05,947
you'll know the abnormality
and weakness of life.

446
00:33:08,119 --> 00:33:09,609
So many lovely children,

447
00:33:10,421 --> 00:33:12,082
they still haven't
seem the future rainbow.

448
00:33:12,890 --> 00:33:15,085
But they have to go through
this kind of torture.

449
00:33:18,029 --> 00:33:20,998
My son is one of them.

450
00:33:22,633 --> 00:33:23,691
A few months later,

451
00:33:24,569 --> 00:33:27,163
we perhaps can't see them again.

452
00:33:30,141 --> 00:33:32,507
My son is waiting for
the bone marrow matching.

453
00:33:33,544 --> 00:33:35,705
By waiting for the coming
of a new life again.

454
00:33:37,181 --> 00:33:38,443
As a mother,

455
00:33:39,517 --> 00:33:42,179
I'm not able to give him a second one.

456
00:33:43,221 --> 00:33:44,620
The only thing I can give him,

457
00:33:45,490 --> 00:33:48,789
is to let him live happily
everyday for the rest of the days.

458
00:33:49,694 --> 00:33:51,719
91; B92; B93; B94

459
00:33:51,896 --> 00:33:54,831
95; B96; B97; B98

460
00:33:54,999 --> 00:33:56,091
99; B100

461
00:33:56,334 --> 00:33:58,359
It's great! Uncle Chan,
you broke the record!

462
00:33:58,770 --> 00:34:02,672
102; B103; B105

463
00:34:04,542 --> 00:34:06,009
Very good.

464
00:34:07,178 --> 00:34:08,372
I've been very busy lately,

465
00:34:08,679 --> 00:34:09,611
so I haven't got time to see you.

466
00:34:10,114 --> 00:34:10,705
Where's Mum?

467
00:34:11,149 --> 00:34:12,207
Mum has gone to hand in the scripts.

468
00:34:12,850 --> 00:34:14,647
Uncle bought you a new
football. Do you like it?

469
00:34:15,186 --> 00:34:16,619
Yes! Thank you!

470
00:34:17,221 --> 00:34:18,984
Uncle, this ball is for adults.

471
00:34:19,223 --> 00:34:20,087
No problem.

472
00:34:20,491 --> 00:34:22,823
You wait until you leave the
hospital. I'll play with you.

473
00:34:23,594 --> 00:34:24,856
Mum, Uncle Chan is here.

474
00:34:28,166 --> 00:34:30,031
Kin Kao, why are you coming?

475
00:34:30,468 --> 00:34:31,526
I specially take a day off

476
00:34:31,702 --> 00:34:32,726
to see Fai.

477
00:34:33,571 --> 00:34:34,037
Thank you.

478
00:34:35,006 --> 00:34:37,406
Fai, it's late. I've to go now.

479
00:34:37,575 --> 00:34:38,542
Goodbye Uncle Chan!

480
00:34:38,709 --> 00:34:40,677
Goodbye! Hope you get well soon!

481
00:34:40,845 --> 00:34:42,142
Thank you Uncle!

482
00:34:43,181 --> 00:34:46,150
Kuen, there's one thing I
want to discuss with you.

483
00:34:47,285 --> 00:34:49,446
Uncle Chan, don't forget
to wait for me to come out

484
00:34:49,620 --> 00:34:50,712
and bring me to play football.

485
00:34:51,155 --> 00:34:51,883
Alright!

486
00:34:53,891 --> 00:34:54,585
Kuen,

487
00:34:54,959 --> 00:34:56,824
this is our police's
colleague a little gratuity.

488
00:34:57,028 --> 00:34:57,858
Hope that you'll accept.

489
00:34:58,229 --> 00:34:59,753
Kin Kao, no...

490
00:34:59,931 --> 00:35:00,829
I can't take this money.

491
00:35:01,132 --> 00:35:03,623
No, I learn from my Mum.

492
00:35:03,901 --> 00:35:05,528
Fai's medical fee is very expensive.

493
00:35:06,204 --> 00:35:07,933
We've contributed about
ten thousand dollars.

494
00:35:08,506 --> 00:35:10,531
It isn't a lot, hope you take it.

495
00:35:14,512 --> 00:35:16,980
Kuen, Fai will be alright, don't worry.

496
00:35:19,350 --> 00:35:21,113
Okay. It's late, I have to go.

497
00:35:21,486 --> 00:35:22,817
Thank you, Kin Kao.

498
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:37,830
Today, I received an appreciative
letter from a little guy in Japan.

499
00:35:38,069 --> 00:35:40,037
He said that he had recovered very well.

500
00:35:40,371 --> 00:35:41,929
He can go home in one
to two month's time.

501
00:35:42,473 --> 00:35:43,405
That's great.

502
00:35:43,774 --> 00:35:45,605
He particularly wanted
to thanks for you.

503
00:35:47,078 --> 00:35:48,045
For what?

504
00:35:48,513 --> 00:35:49,537
Especially is to you.

505
00:35:50,047 --> 00:35:51,036
And also Allen, the bone marrow donor.

506
00:35:52,283 --> 00:35:54,547
You see, he also sent
us this pair of doll.

507
00:35:54,919 --> 00:35:56,853
It's lovely! Very lovely!

508
00:36:02,693 --> 00:36:03,785
Officer...

509
00:36:04,495 --> 00:36:05,393
News just came from Shenyang that

510
00:36:05,630 --> 00:36:06,858
they found a couple of right matches.

511
00:36:07,064 --> 00:36:07,758
It's great! For who?

512
00:36:07,932 --> 00:36:08,694
Luk Fai.

513
00:36:08,900 --> 00:36:09,696
Who is the donor?

514
00:36:09,867 --> 00:36:11,391
A lady called Wong Mei.

515
00:36:11,802 --> 00:36:13,827
She is 32 years old and is a Librarian.

516
00:36:14,038 --> 00:36:15,596
Good, very good. Yes.

517
00:36:16,374 --> 00:36:17,466
But before it's confirmed,

518
00:36:17,742 --> 00:36:19,505
don't tell the relatives
about this news.

519
00:36:19,777 --> 00:36:20,243
Okay.

520
00:36:20,478 --> 00:36:22,912
Donor's will is also a problem.

521
00:36:23,347 --> 00:36:25,542
So, we've to contact the
other side immediately.

522
00:36:25,716 --> 00:36:26,614
Okay.

523
00:36:27,618 --> 00:36:30,849
SHEN YANG

524
00:36:36,460 --> 00:36:37,392
How do you do, doctor.

525
00:36:37,595 --> 00:36:38,721
I am Wong Mei.

526
00:36:38,963 --> 00:36:39,691
Fine. I'm Lee Chung.

527
00:36:39,864 --> 00:36:40,728
Fine, Dr Lee.

528
00:36:41,966 --> 00:36:44,093
I can't imagine...
You're a pregnant woman.

529
00:36:44,735 --> 00:36:46,362
Does it matter?

530
00:36:47,338 --> 00:36:49,806
It's okay. I think to save a
person's life is more important.

531
00:36:50,441 --> 00:36:51,533
Of course, it's a top priority
to save a person's life.

532
00:36:52,109 --> 00:36:53,770
But both yourself and your child's
safety are also very important

533
00:36:54,946 --> 00:36:56,675
Although there're examples of pregnant
women having bone marrow extraction.

534
00:36:57,215 --> 00:36:59,410
However, if there's any possibility
causing harm to the baby,

535
00:36:59,584 --> 00:37:00,676
we'd better try to avoid it.

536
00:37:01,219 --> 00:37:02,379
We do appreciate you very much.

537
00:37:03,387 --> 00:37:04,684
It's a pity that I can't help.

538
00:37:04,855 --> 00:37:05,549
Thank you.

539
00:37:30,848 --> 00:37:32,975
I learnt that Luk Fai
had a high temperature.

540
00:37:33,584 --> 00:37:34,846
Luckily, he's okay.

541
00:37:37,421 --> 00:37:39,116
For children who got
this kind of diseases

542
00:37:39,757 --> 00:37:41,622
is really something cry one's heart out.

543
00:37:44,295 --> 00:37:45,387
Sometimes,

544
00:37:46,497 --> 00:37:49,591
I don't know whether
I can take it anymore.

545
00:37:52,336 --> 00:37:54,236
Please let me cry now,

546
00:37:55,239 --> 00:37:56,729
I have no more tears.

547
00:37:58,776 --> 00:38:00,505
When facing this kind of thing,

548
00:38:01,279 --> 00:38:04,942
we as mothers have no other choice.

549
00:38:06,150 --> 00:38:08,675
We can only do our best.

550
00:38:10,688 --> 00:38:14,180
So my advice to you, is to take it easy.

551
00:38:21,599 --> 00:38:23,760
I went to see a Chinese
doctor a few days ago.

552
00:38:24,735 --> 00:38:27,727
He persuaded me to make use of
the western medical treatment.

553
00:38:28,406 --> 00:38:31,034
He said bone marrow transplant
method is the last resort.

554
00:38:33,077 --> 00:38:34,738
You see Chinese medical
doctor also believes in it.

555
00:38:36,047 --> 00:38:39,608
Is there any other alternative?

556
00:38:41,986 --> 00:38:43,851
Now, I only know

557
00:38:44,021 --> 00:38:46,922
Dr Lee is a very trust worth person.

558
00:38:48,993 --> 00:38:50,620
He treats other people's children

559
00:38:51,195 --> 00:38:54,062
like his own.

560
00:38:56,400 --> 00:39:00,996
It's more than half a
year, if there's no him,

561
00:39:02,573 --> 00:39:05,508
I'm afraid I can't last till today.

562
00:39:08,079 --> 00:39:09,341
I do trust him.

563
00:39:10,114 --> 00:39:11,843
If he can't even save Yin Yin...

564
00:39:12,650 --> 00:39:16,677
I think this is fate.

565
00:39:22,226 --> 00:39:23,989
So, for both of us,

566
00:39:24,829 --> 00:39:26,626
only persistent.

567
00:39:27,098 --> 00:39:30,829
Persistent is the only way.

568
00:39:35,740 --> 00:39:36,900
Luckily,

569
00:39:37,608 --> 00:39:41,305
Yin Yin is a very
mature kid in the family.

570
00:39:42,480 --> 00:39:45,779
Sometimes, she even comfort me.

571
00:39:47,051 --> 00:39:47,449
She said...

572
00:39:47,618 --> 00:39:51,145
Mum, you have to hold on to it.

573
00:39:51,655 --> 00:39:52,952
You must hold on.

574
00:40:28,726 --> 00:40:31,251
It isn't easy to come to see a picture.

575
00:40:31,695 --> 00:40:32,719
Can't you relax a bit?

576
00:40:33,230 --> 00:40:34,822
Please put aside the
work for the time being.

577
00:40:35,099 --> 00:40:35,997
Since there're still half an hour to go,

578
00:40:36,167 --> 00:40:37,964
you wait here, I'll be ready soon.

579
00:40:39,003 --> 00:40:40,595
But your Mum wanted
me to take care of you.

580
00:40:40,871 --> 00:40:41,929
If you were tired to death,

581
00:40:42,239 --> 00:40:43,604
what shall I tell your Mum?

582
00:40:43,941 --> 00:40:45,772
I think you've done a good job.

583
00:40:46,577 --> 00:40:49,068
No, have a rest first.

584
00:40:49,447 --> 00:40:50,277
Have your eyes closed,

585
00:40:51,382 --> 00:40:53,247
rest for a while.

586
00:40:54,051 --> 00:40:55,541
Okay, then.

587
00:40:58,756 --> 00:40:59,484
Happy Birthday!

588
00:41:00,958 --> 00:41:02,152
You still remember my birthday!

589
00:41:02,326 --> 00:41:03,953
Of course. I don't even remember myself.

590
00:41:04,428 --> 00:41:05,452
It's very pretty!

591
00:41:06,897 --> 00:41:07,864
Your heart...

592
00:41:08,232 --> 00:41:09,995
all devoted to the Care Unit

593
00:41:10,568 --> 00:41:11,796
I almost forgot.

594
00:41:12,436 --> 00:41:13,300
How can it be?

595
00:41:14,038 --> 00:41:15,596
It's very pretty, thank you!

596
00:41:21,512 --> 00:41:22,877
Luk Fai's match!

597
00:41:23,247 --> 00:41:24,236
This is no. 19 already!

598
00:41:24,415 --> 00:41:25,404
Go back quickly!

599
00:41:26,951 --> 00:41:27,713
But...

600
00:41:28,219 --> 00:41:29,277
in that case, our film will be over.

601
00:41:29,587 --> 00:41:30,417
See it next time.

602
00:41:31,622 --> 00:41:34,853
TAITUNG PRISON

603
00:42:00,284 --> 00:42:01,945
Are you Mr Ng Sung Yung?

604
00:42:03,954 --> 00:42:06,013
Sorry, I've seen your information.

605
00:42:06,657 --> 00:42:08,488
You born in 1959.

606
00:42:09,994 --> 00:42:11,256
What's matter?

607
00:42:12,730 --> 00:42:13,958
We sent you this flower.

608
00:42:14,331 --> 00:42:15,457
Hope you can get out
from the prison soon!

609
00:42:17,234 --> 00:42:19,202
I'm Suen Yan Yan

610
00:42:19,370 --> 00:42:20,098
from the Care Unit of Taipei Hospital.

611
00:42:23,007 --> 00:42:24,065
The things is

612
00:42:24,742 --> 00:42:26,403
there is a boy from
Beijing, called Luk Fai.

613
00:42:26,610 --> 00:42:27,474
He has haemophilia.

614
00:42:27,978 --> 00:42:29,138
He probably can survive

615
00:42:29,947 --> 00:42:31,380
for another half year.

616
00:42:31,949 --> 00:42:33,348
This's why he needed the bone
marrow transplant urgently.

617
00:42:34,018 --> 00:42:35,349
My bone marrow?

618
00:42:35,753 --> 00:42:37,846
Yes, it was September 12 last year

619
00:42:38,088 --> 00:42:39,851
Didn't you have the blood
donation at Kaohsiung?

620
00:42:40,190 --> 00:42:41,748
You're very lucky!

621
00:42:42,259 --> 00:42:43,487
There're so many people
have the blood donation.

622
00:42:43,661 --> 00:42:44,992
But, the chance to match
successfully is slim.

623
00:42:45,396 --> 00:42:46,055
For you,

624
00:42:46,230 --> 00:42:48,289
you can even save a person's
life in such a short time.

625
00:42:48,666 --> 00:42:49,860
So, you're really very lucky!

626
00:42:50,134 --> 00:42:51,396
I really feel happy for you.

627
00:42:52,036 --> 00:42:53,936
You shouldn't be happy too
early as I didn't say to donate.

628
00:42:54,138 --> 00:42:55,070
Why?

629
00:42:55,406 --> 00:42:58,068
You were volunteer for the blood
donation and wish to help people yourself.

630
00:42:58,676 --> 00:42:59,938
That was at that time only.

631
00:43:00,144 --> 00:43:01,133
I was able to go round
everywhere at that time.

632
00:43:01,312 --> 00:43:02,643
I'd never expect.

633
00:43:04,048 --> 00:43:05,310
Mr Ng, but...

634
00:43:05,482 --> 00:43:07,313
So what? Shit!

635
00:43:07,685 --> 00:43:08,242
In my life,

636
00:43:08,419 --> 00:43:09,909
this was the first time in
jail of such poor condition!

637
00:43:11,488 --> 00:43:12,648
I wanted to be a good man.

638
00:43:12,856 --> 00:43:13,914
Also, my business was doing not bad.

639
00:43:14,425 --> 00:43:16,723
He talked about things
which were ages ago.

640
00:43:16,927 --> 00:43:17,894
Then, I was taken here somehow.

641
00:43:18,228 --> 00:43:19,286
Mr Ng...

642
00:43:21,732 --> 00:43:24,530
Mr Ng, would you please
consider it again?

643
00:43:31,342 --> 00:43:32,832
There's no need to be unhappy.

644
00:43:35,179 --> 00:43:36,237
How come?

645
00:43:36,880 --> 00:43:39,041
At first, it was a pregnant woman.

646
00:43:39,683 --> 00:43:40,945
Now, this guy is like that.

647
00:43:42,086 --> 00:43:43,018
What can Luk Fai do?

648
00:43:43,754 --> 00:43:44,721
There must be a way.

649
00:43:45,155 --> 00:43:46,144
Is there any other way?

650
00:43:46,890 --> 00:43:48,790
You should know how difficult
it is to get the right matching.

651
00:43:49,660 --> 00:43:50,991
It's already not easy to get two so far.

652
00:43:51,462 --> 00:43:52,429
But now the situation is like that.

653
00:43:53,297 --> 00:43:56,858
It could be that Ng Sung
Yung, has been kept too long.

654
00:43:57,201 --> 00:43:58,862
Thus, his mood is a bit change.

655
00:43:59,370 --> 00:44:01,838
He probably will change
his mind later on.

656
00:44:03,474 --> 00:44:04,441
I also don't know.

657
00:44:05,242 --> 00:44:08,109
He only said to me he wanted
to be a good person at first,

658
00:44:08,479 --> 00:44:09,673
but this society didn't
give him a chance.

659
00:44:10,180 --> 00:44:11,772
Thus, he became a bad guy.

660
00:44:14,518 --> 00:44:16,509
As he went for the blood
donation, it showed that...

661
00:44:16,754 --> 00:44:18,449
he did wanted to help people.

662
00:44:19,790 --> 00:44:23,419
He said that he donated
blood for running only.

663
00:44:23,594 --> 00:44:26,028
So he didn't know what made
him donate blood originally.

664
00:44:27,297 --> 00:44:28,127
Really?

665
00:44:29,433 --> 00:44:30,593
Then, what can we do?

666
00:44:31,669 --> 00:44:32,658
Try again.

667
00:44:34,872 --> 00:44:36,066
I won't give it up.

668
00:44:38,242 --> 00:44:40,540
I've spent so much money on you.

669
00:44:40,778 --> 00:44:44,339
Lying ill in bed but who
would bring me medicine.

670
00:44:44,581 --> 00:44:46,811
Hung Shun died but life remains alive.

671
00:44:47,184 --> 00:44:50,881
Slaves... Ah... Slaves

672
00:44:51,689 --> 00:45:00,722
Worrying that arrows will
punch through your body

673
00:45:00,898 --> 00:45:10,102
And your body buried no where

674
00:45:10,708 --> 00:45:13,336
Great! Good!

675
00:45:15,245 --> 00:45:16,610
Kids, be quiet.

676
00:45:16,780 --> 00:45:17,542
I know, Auntie.

677
00:45:17,715 --> 00:45:18,704
Good boy.

678
00:45:21,919 --> 00:45:23,284
Thank you for coming to see me.

679
00:45:23,654 --> 00:45:24,882
When can you be discharge?

680
00:45:25,122 --> 00:45:27,090
Fai, where has your blood gone?

681
00:45:27,524 --> 00:45:29,185
What does this mean?

682
00:45:30,260 --> 00:45:31,852
All the adults have the
blood transfusion for you.

683
00:45:32,963 --> 00:45:33,861
I don't need blood transfusion.

684
00:45:34,631 --> 00:45:36,223
We also have to do the
blood transfusion for you.

685
00:45:37,534 --> 00:45:39,729
Donate what? I wasn't injured.

686
00:45:40,104 --> 00:45:41,503
You'd better ask your Mum.

687
00:45:48,879 --> 00:45:50,369
Why are you touching my head?

688
00:45:51,782 --> 00:45:53,272
Is it...

689
00:45:53,450 --> 00:45:55,543
those who are bald will go to heaven.

690
00:45:56,520 --> 00:45:57,748
What do you mean by going to heaven?

691
00:45:58,388 --> 00:46:00,288
Silly guy, it means dead.

692
00:46:00,758 --> 00:46:02,191
It can't be.

693
00:46:02,893 --> 00:46:04,190
Will your hair shed?

694
00:46:04,962 --> 00:46:06,293
Fai, do you have this disease?

695
00:46:07,631 --> 00:46:09,030
What kind of disease have I got?

696
00:46:09,433 --> 00:46:10,422
Didn't your Mum tell you?

697
00:46:12,703 --> 00:46:13,863
But, I learnt from my Grandma,

698
00:46:14,171 --> 00:46:16,696
yours is haemophilia
disease, a serious one.

699
00:46:16,974 --> 00:46:18,703
It's cancer...

700
00:46:22,546 --> 00:46:23,638
So, what can we do?

701
00:46:26,483 --> 00:46:27,609
That's enough, let's go.

702
00:46:27,785 --> 00:46:28,683
Good-bye, Fai!

703
00:46:28,852 --> 00:46:31,116
See you tomorrow.

704
00:46:36,727 --> 00:46:38,285
No...

705
00:46:38,462 --> 00:46:39,486
I don't want to have my
head shaved. Please don't!

706
00:46:39,663 --> 00:46:41,290
I don't want my hair to
get shed. I don't want it!

707
00:46:41,665 --> 00:46:45,362
Please don't! I don't want
to have my head shaved...

708
00:46:53,477 --> 00:46:56,571
Yung, you have to take it easy.

709
00:46:57,481 --> 00:47:00,882
Our life have almost gone half way.

710
00:47:02,820 --> 00:47:04,811
We've been going in and out
from the prison all the way.

711
00:47:06,456 --> 00:47:10,256
Honestly, what a waste of our life!

712
00:47:12,462 --> 00:47:14,726
People outside treat
us like waste material.

713
00:47:16,667 --> 00:47:21,366
Our family have no one to respect them.

714
00:47:23,340 --> 00:47:26,969
In the end, it's already too late.

715
00:47:28,679 --> 00:47:30,112
We can't go back and
start all over again.

716
00:47:31,148 --> 00:47:33,810
Why don't we do something meaningful?

717
00:47:34,952 --> 00:47:38,479
At least this can relieve
your uneasy feelings inside.

718
00:47:41,925 --> 00:47:42,983
You think about it.

719
00:47:44,328 --> 00:47:45,693
If this kid without you,

720
00:47:46,430 --> 00:47:48,261
he probably can't even
see the sun tomorrow.

721
00:47:51,268 --> 00:47:53,532
Just assume that your
ancestor owed them.

722
00:47:56,907 --> 00:48:02,937
If you don't speak it out

723
00:48:03,881 --> 00:48:08,750
No one knows

724
00:48:09,987 --> 00:48:15,892
Sometimes, it needs to air-out

725
00:48:16,693 --> 00:48:23,257
A full chest of sorrow

726
00:48:29,873 --> 00:48:31,067
Do you like swan?

727
00:48:32,576 --> 00:48:34,476
Okay, and you?

728
00:48:35,178 --> 00:48:36,008
Yes, I like.

729
00:48:36,813 --> 00:48:38,713
I hope I can be the same as swan.

730
00:48:39,549 --> 00:48:40,777
I can fly to the sky.

731
00:48:41,485 --> 00:48:44,750
Then, I have no more
vaccinations and medicine.

732
00:48:45,889 --> 00:48:47,720
But your Mum can't find you.

733
00:48:48,759 --> 00:48:49,851
If I were there,

734
00:48:50,193 --> 00:48:52,627
Mum didn't have to worry about me.

735
00:48:53,764 --> 00:48:54,992
What sort of a place?

736
00:48:55,999 --> 00:48:57,523
Place where swans go.

737
00:48:59,369 --> 00:49:00,358
Can I go as well?

738
00:49:00,737 --> 00:49:01,567
I don't know.

739
00:49:02,506 --> 00:49:04,770
If you had the right
bone marrow matching,

740
00:49:05,242 --> 00:49:08,734
you could stay with your Mum.

741
00:49:09,880 --> 00:49:11,108
Can I go to see you?

742
00:49:11,848 --> 00:49:14,681
No, you can't come back.

743
00:49:15,552 --> 00:49:16,712
Is the place very far away?

744
00:49:22,192 --> 00:49:23,750
It's just above there.

745
00:49:24,227 --> 00:49:25,319
Above the blue sky.

746
00:50:26,923 --> 00:50:29,221
Yin Yin, how do you feel? Yin Yin...

747
00:50:29,393 --> 00:50:30,951
Yin Yin, what happen to you?

748
00:50:31,161 --> 00:50:32,128
Yin Yin, wake up!

749
00:50:32,896 --> 00:50:34,557
Yin Yin...

750
00:50:36,066 --> 00:50:37,863
Yin Yin, wake up!

751
00:50:41,438 --> 00:50:42,837
Yin Yin, wake up!

752
00:50:45,142 --> 00:50:47,610
Yin Yin...

753
00:50:47,778 --> 00:50:50,406
Help...

754
00:50:50,580 --> 00:50:52,810
Help! Help!

755
00:50:57,020 --> 00:50:58,578
Nurse!

756
00:50:59,723 --> 00:51:01,384
Nurse, Yin Yin's fainted!

757
00:51:01,825 --> 00:51:02,314
What happen?

758
00:51:02,492 --> 00:51:03,322
Yin Yin has fainted!

759
00:51:43,767 --> 00:51:46,395
Auntie, has Yin Yin passed away?

760
00:51:54,511 --> 00:51:57,378
Auntie, will I be the same as Yin Yin?

761
00:51:57,747 --> 00:52:00,910
Once I became bald, I'd go
to a very far away place.

762
00:52:03,353 --> 00:52:04,411
Auntie, don't cry.

763
00:52:05,388 --> 00:52:06,685
Yin Yin said there was no need to cry.

764
00:52:11,228 --> 00:52:12,718
What else did she tell you?

765
00:52:13,430 --> 00:52:15,898
She would go to a place
where she could dance everyday

766
00:52:16,066 --> 00:52:17,624
and wouldn't get sick.

767
00:52:18,502 --> 00:52:19,628
So, you shouldn't cry.

768
00:52:20,971 --> 00:52:22,404
Auntie...

769
00:52:25,142 --> 00:52:26,200
Auntie, don't worry.

770
00:52:26,943 --> 00:52:27,910
I'll go to see her.

771
00:53:11,955 --> 00:53:14,822
Grandpa...

772
00:53:18,061 --> 00:53:22,293
Grandpa, you'd better
hold up you thumb quickly.

773
00:53:25,302 --> 00:53:29,136
Grandpa, this might be
the last time I help you.

774
00:53:30,006 --> 00:53:32,873
Grandpa, don't worry.

775
00:53:33,376 --> 00:53:35,003
Mum will help you in the future.

776
00:53:37,047 --> 00:53:39,242
Grandpa, I've to go.

777
00:53:39,983 --> 00:53:42,747
You know, I got a very serious illness

778
00:53:44,054 --> 00:53:45,681
and soon will get bald.

779
00:53:46,256 --> 00:53:49,487
Then, I'll go to another
place same as Yin Yin.

780
00:53:50,994 --> 00:53:53,155
Grandpa, I don't want
to go to the hospital.

781
00:53:54,097 --> 00:53:56,964
I'm scare. I've to hide myself.

782
00:53:58,201 --> 00:54:00,533
Grandpa, please don't tell Mum.

783
00:54:01,504 --> 00:54:02,937
I have to hide myself.

784
00:54:03,473 --> 00:54:06,306
So, they can't take me away.

785
00:54:22,325 --> 00:54:23,451
Mum

786
00:54:25,829 --> 00:54:27,990
Why were you running out
from the hospital secretly?

787
00:54:29,566 --> 00:54:31,557
I miss Grandpa. I don't want
to go back to the hospital.

788
00:54:34,704 --> 00:54:36,137
But your illness hasn't been cured yet.

789
00:54:37,540 --> 00:54:38,529
I'm not ill.

790
00:54:42,212 --> 00:54:44,442
Let's wait for the medical result first.

791
00:54:44,814 --> 00:54:46,042
You still haven't
finished the checking up.

792
00:54:49,653 --> 00:54:51,518
Please hold on for a few more days.

793
00:54:52,055 --> 00:54:53,113
Only a few more days, okay?

794
00:54:54,691 --> 00:54:58,559
Mum, I don't want to have
my head shaved. I'm scare.

795
00:54:58,928 --> 00:55:00,156
Shave your head?

796
00:55:00,964 --> 00:55:02,261
Who said that?

797
00:55:03,533 --> 00:55:04,727
Yin Yin shaved hers.

798
00:55:05,368 --> 00:55:06,995
Then, she died afterwards.

799
00:55:08,338 --> 00:55:09,236
Don't talk nonsense!

